# git-gpg-sign-email-mismatch-silent-unsigned-blocks-merge — History

## v2.1.0 (2026-06-06)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus PRs #1021 / #1026 — pr-policy "every commit is signed" failed at merge despite locally-good signatures
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed

- Expanded `description:` to cover four new failure modes: (d) `+suffix` noreply
  emails cannot be verified on a GitHub account so adding them as a key UID does NOT
  fix `no_user`; (e) bare `git commit -S` picking the wrong default key (`%G?`=`E`);
  (f) a silently-aborted commit (non-zero pre-commit hook) leaving HEAD unchanged and
  masquerading as corruption; plus the pr-policy "every commit is signed" gate framing.
- Added five new "When to Use" triggers (bot email in global gitconfig; do-not-patch-key
  warning; `--show-signature` lying about merge-readiness; building re-sign tooling).
- Added new Verified Workflow subsection "GitHub +suffix noreply Emails Cannot Be
  Verified — Do NOT Patch the Key" with the verifiable-email-shape table.
- Added new Verified Workflow subsection "Always Pass the Signing Key Explicitly;
  Re-Verify HEAD After Every Commit".
- Added new Verified Workflow subsection "Defensive Tooling: Validate Resign Email
  Against Key UIDs Before Batch Re-Sign" (`fleet_sync.get_resign_email()`,
  `FLEET_SKIP_EMAIL_KEY_CHECK=1` bypass).
- Added Failed Attempts 9-12 (trusting `--show-signature`; patching key UID with a
  `+suffix` email; bare `git commit -S` picking a foreign key; silent commit abort
  read as corruption).
- Refined the `no_user` row in the verification reason table.
- Added 2026-06-06 ProjectHephaestus entry to Verified On.
- Bumped to v2.1.0.

### Why

On ProjectHephaestus (PRs #1021 / #1026) commits signed fine locally
(`git log --show-signature` => "Good signature", `%G?`=`G`) but GitHub returned
`verification: {verified:false, reason:"no_user"}` and the `pr-policy` "every commit
is signed" check FAILED at merge. Root cause: the global `~/.gitconfig` `user.email`
was a BOT identity (`mvillmow+bot@users.noreply.github.com`) inherited by hand-authored
commits, while the GPG key (`F0A2530669A31A2E`, signing subkey `7FD616C4744A8A7C`) was
bound only to `4211002+mvillmow@users.noreply.github.com`. Agent-authored commits
already used the correct email and verified fine.

KEY NEW INSIGHT: a GitHub `+suffix` noreply variant cannot be added/verified on an
account (only `{id}+{username}@users.noreply.github.com` and real verified emails
work), so the `no_user` failure CANNOT be fixed by adding the bot email as a key UID —
GitHub still returns `no_user`. The working fixes are to set the committer email to the
key's registered address (then `git commit --amend --reset-author -S`) or to make
automation author commits with a verifiable email. A defensive guard was added in
`fleet_sync.get_resign_email()` to validate the resolved resign email against the key's
UID emails before a fleet rebase re-signs many commits.

These learnings share the same search surface as v2.0.0 (PR-merge blocked by signing /
`no_user`) but add distinct root causes and fixes, hence a minor bump.

